The nematodes from various type of deciduous forests, such as oak (
Quercus petraea , Q. robur
), beech (
Fagus sylvatica
with
Quercus spp .
), lime-ash (
Tilia tomentosa , T. cordata, Fraxinus excelsior
), oak-hornbeam (
Quercus petraea, Carpinus betulus
), maple-hornbeam (
Acer campester , A. platanoides, Carpinus betulus
) and mixed forests, have been studied for more than ten years. This paper is based on all the existed data on soil nematodes found in the deciduous forests of Moldova.
